               <strong class="title1">Dear friends and colleagues, dear guests,</strong>   <br />&nbsp;
                        <br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; three years have passed quickly and Slovak paediatric surgeons have the honour to organize
the 57th Congress of Slovak and Czech paediatric surgeons with international participation. With
regard to the positive feedback from the congress organized in Vrátna dolina in the Malá Fatra
Mountains, our choice of the venue was very easy, we picked the place of our next congress in
a beautiful surroundings of Slovak nature, which the Low Tatras and Jasná undoubtedly are. The
scenery of the Low Tatras landscape covered in sun and snow offers a unique coulisse for various
professional events and an opportunity to enjoy oneself, after a demanding scientific work. It
definitely is an exceptional atmosphere, for which we have virtually no time in our every-day
medical practice. The great mix of business with pleasure is ensured not only by selection of the
natural scenery of the north side of the Low Tatras, but also by the very venue of the Congress
– Wellness Chopok Hotel, which offers both modern space and technical conference facilities, as
well as a wide scale of high-quality opportunities for relaxation. The local gastronomy based on
Slovak and international cuisine specialties is another strong point of the facility that no guest
would question.
Same as previous years, the 57th Congress is a concrete result of historical continuity of
many-sided close relationships of Slovaks and Czechs, guarantee of high professional level of
the event, and a suitable opportunity to continue in and further develop cooperation in the area
of paediatric surgery. Last but not least, it is a place of meeting of long-time colleagues, friends
and an important platform for both professional and social entrenchment of the upcoming
generation of paediatric surgeons. Participation of invited speakers from other EU countries
gives the Congress the needed dimension of constructive dialogue about the level and current
trends in the area of paediatric surgery in a wider European context.
We are looking forward to your participation, and we do believe that first-time visitors to the Low
Tatras will find there an inspiration for many returns as well as a closer exploration of this magical
corner of Slovakia. Moreover, those of you who know Demänovská dolina (Valley), are going to
enjoy their stay enriched with pleasant experiences and unforgettable memories. <br />
